        ﾜﾜﾜ  ﾜ ﾟｲｲﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛｲﾟ
        ｲｲｲ ﾜ ﾟﾜ  ﾟﾟｲﾜ
       ﾟﾟﾟﾟ  ﾛ ｲｲ  ﾜ  ﾟ    
   ｰｱｲﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾛﾟ ﾜﾟ  ﾟｲﾟ     Release notes:
        ﾜﾜﾜ
        ﾛﾛﾛ   As Machine Learning explodes in popularity, it is becoming
        ﾛﾛﾛ   ever more important to know precisely how to frame a
        ﾛﾛﾛ   machine learning model in a manner appropriate to the
        ﾛﾛﾛ   problem we are trying to solve, and the data that we have
        ﾛﾛﾛ   available. 

In this course, Creating Machine Learning
        ﾛﾛﾛ   Models you will gain the ability to choose the right type
        ﾛﾛﾛ   of model for your problem, then build that model, and
        ﾛﾛﾛ   evaluate its performance. 

First, you will learn how rule-
        ﾛﾛﾛ   based and ML-based systems differ and their strengths and
        ﾛﾛﾛ   weaknesses and how supervised and unsupervised learning
        ﾛﾛﾛ   models differ from each other. 

Next, you will discover
        ﾛﾛﾛ   how to implement a range of techniques to solve the
        ﾛﾛﾛ   supervised learning problems of classification and
        ﾛﾛﾛ   regression. You will gain an intuitive understanding of the
        ﾛﾛﾛ   the model algorithms you can use for classification and
        ﾛﾛﾛ   regression. Finally, you will round out your knowledge by
        ﾛﾛﾛ   building clustering models using a couple of different
        ﾛﾛﾛ   algorithms, and validating the results. 

When you池e
        ﾛﾛﾛ   finished with this course, you will have the skills and
        ﾛﾛﾛ   knowledge to identify the correct machine learning problem
        ﾛﾛﾛ   setup, and the appropriate solution and evaluation
        ﾛﾛﾛ   techniques for your use-case.
